# A hole whose seed is a (T, error)-returning call directly (no |> pipeline
# stage involved) inside a Go-expression js literal: same "no error channel in
# an expression position" rejection as diag_error_pipe.txtar, exercised via
# the tuple-unwrap path in embeddedHoleExpr instead of pipelineHasErr.
-- input.gsx --
package demo

func risky() (string, error) { return "x", nil }

var h = js`f(@{risky()})`

component Page() {
	<button @click={h}>x</button>
}
-- invoke --
Page()
-- diagnostics.golden --
5:15: @{ risky() } returns (string, error); a js`/css`/f` literal in Go-expression position has no error channel to propagate it through — handle the error in Go, or move the literal to an attribute position
